                            <comment id="13472290" author="pellcorp" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 12:04:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;further test to ensure its not a jaxws version problem.  Reverted back to jaxws 2.1 still same issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13472292" author="pellcorp" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 12:05:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In order to see this issue you need to force SoapUI to always use MTOM.  the src/test/resources soapui project does that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13472299" author="pellcorp" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 12:30:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This problem occurs only when using IN or BOTH.  If you use &apos;true&apos; the problem does not occur.  Its a regression caused by the enhancement&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13472305" author="pellcorp" created="Tue, 9 Oct 2012 12:35:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I am not sure whether 3813 should be re-opened and listed as incomplete or if the patch to fix the regression should be provided against this issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Some advice from devs would be good&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
